==English==

===Etymology===
For adjective: From {{etyl|fro}} {{term|rationel}}, {{term|rational|lang=fro}} < {{etyl|la}} {{term|rationalis||of or belonging to reason, rational, reasonable}} < {{term|ratio||reason}}

For noun: From {{etyl|fro}} {{term|rational|lang=fro}} < {{ML.}} {{term|rationale||a pontifical stole, a pallium, an ornament worn over the chasuble}}, neut. of {{etyl|la}} {{term|rationalis||rational}}, for which see the first etymology.

